# Spectral — Military Drone Intelligence Platform

## What This Is
Spectral is a commercial SaaS military drone intelligence platform built by David (A3DM founder) to sell to defence training providers and contractors. It is a **standalone product** — OSINT-only, ITAR-compliant, no air gap required.

## Seven Core Modules
1. **Platform Library** — world military UAS database (39+ platforms, all tiers)
2. **Spectrum View** — EW spectrum visualiser (D3.js log-scale, 400 MHz–6 GHz)
3. **GNSS Intelligence** — jamming/spoofing threat map, constellation status, defeat methods
4. **Defeat Matrix** — platform × c-UAS effector capability grid
5. **Conflict Intel** — live case studies (Ukraine, Red Sea, Nagorno-Karabakh, India-Pakistan)
6. **Red/Blue Arena** — 3D adversarial scenario engine (CesiumJS globe)
7. **1v1 Overlay** — single drone vs single counter-system comparison

## Classification Banner
Every page renders the banner at the top:
```
UNCLASSIFIED // FOR OFFICIAL TRAINING USE ONLY
```
This is non-negotiable on every route. See `app/globals.css` for `.classification-banner` class.

## Audience
Defence training providers, contractors, allied military liaison staff, Five Eyes and friendly nations (SG, ID, UAE, JP, EU partners).

## Data Policy
- All data is **OSINT only** — no classified sources
- ITAR compliance: no export-controlled technical data in the database
- Seed data: `spectral_seed_data.json` (39 UAS platforms, 5 GNSS constellations, 12 jammers, 12 anti-drone systems, 7 conflict case studies, 9 nav countermeasures)

## Owner Context
David is a 22-year RAAF veteran, ATPL(A)/CPL(H), B737/777/787 and C-17/C-130 operator, current Chief Remote Pilot (DREPL). He is also the developer of A3DM (Next.js 14, 170+ Supabase tables, CesiumJS, ~150K LOC). Talk to him as a senior peer. Do not over-explain aviation or military concepts.

